INSERT INTO `cache_filter` VALUES ('5:d4dace3043657a2fa5d265c2b520cf52','<p><strong>April 2010 ~ Gloster Valley Commemoration </strong><br />BASS members are invited to join veterans and their families to commemorate the actions of British and Commonwealth forces during the Korean War.You must register to attend! RSVP at <a href=\"mailto:basseoul@yahoo.co.uk\">basseoul@yahoo.co.uk</a><br /><br /><strong>May 2010 ~ The Queen\'s Birthday Ball </strong><br />The Queen\'s Birthday Ball is the most glamorous night-out in the British Association\'s calendar and it is also our biggest fundraising event of the year. Come and dance the night away for a cause.You must register to attend! RSVP at <a href=\"mailto:basseoul@yahoo.co.uk\">basseoul@yahoo.co.uk</a><br /><br /><strong>September 2010 ~ The Enchanted Evening </strong><br />The Enchanted Evening is held in the beautiful grounds of the British Embassy to welcome back those returning after the summer and all those new to Seoul. You must register to attend! Open to members only. RSVP at <a href=\"mailto:basseoul@yahoo.co.uk\">basseoul@yahoo.co.uk</a><br /><br /><strong>November 2010 ~ Christmas Fair </strong><br />Come and join our annual Christmas Fair featuring imported British foods, home baked goods and much more. Enjoy some relaxed Christmas shopping over a glass of mulled wine. Open to everybody!<br /><br /><strong>December 2010 ~ BASS Christmas Lunch </strong><br />Don\'t miss one of the merriest events in our Association\'s calendar! We hold our Christmas Lunch early December each year. A fabulous, glamorous event including entertainment, fun and games, sumptuous lunch and a chance to win some exciting prizes. You must register to attend! RSVP at <a href=\"mailto:basseoul@yahoo.co.uk\">basseoul@yahoo.co.uk</a><br /><br /><strong>December 2010 ~ Mince Pie Morning </strong><br />Members are treated to a carol service by children from the British School at the Embassy residence. Enjoy mince pies and other festive treats on offer. You must register to attend! Open to members only. RSVP at <a href=\"mailto:basseoul@yahoo.co.uk\">basseoul@yahoo.co.uk</a></p>\n',1267839037,1267752637,'',0);
INSERT INTO `cache_filter` VALUES ('5:619d344963a0da8d5395a653acffa791','<p>Every year, the Queen\'s Birthday Ball is the most glamorous night-out in the British Association\'s calendar. It is also our major fund-raiser. We are proud to have the generous support of many sponsors from the Seoul business community. Some sponsors provide the goods and services we need to run this fantastic event. Others support our nominated charities directly by donating of cash.<br /><br />Every year the theme of the Ball is kept a secret, until the doors are opened to admit the 500 guests to the amazing ballroom. The theme is always connected with our British heritage and on 30 May 2009, the Grand Ballroom of The Grand Hyatt Hotel was transformed into The Great British Seaside. The Ballroom was decorated with colourful beach huts, Union Jack bunting and giant ice-cream cones and guests were entertained with barbershop singing by the The Lightyears.<br /><br />The roast beef dinner was followed by a live auction of Manchester United items, Korean art and a signed golf jacket. Big prizes in The Grand Raffle were drawn and then guests poured onto the dance-floor for two storming sets from The Lightyears, who performed on a mock-up of the entrance to Brighton Pier.<br /><br />There are some great photos of the evening on this website.<br /><br />If you would like to sponsor this event in 2010, please contact us. There are many ways we can work together to give much-needed assistance to the under-privileged whilst also providing the international community with one of its best nights out.</p>\n',1267839040,1267752640,'',0);
